rComments: Very good prof. Allows lots of time to answer questions in class. There are quite a few group projects which take place during class hours.
Awesome prof, interesting lectures with fun activities. Would definitely take class with professor Elliott again.

Elliot is literally the best prof at Telfer. You will never get bored at her class. She is always smiling and has a positive attitude. She gives great examples to students to make the material relatable. Class activities are so much fun and she grades very fairly. The Midterm and final extremely easy. Highly recommend. (Fall 2019)
Reading textbook is the key to success for this class. The prof is a nice person but spends nearly half the class playing "group activity" games, which is a waste of time.

Really nice professor who cares about her students. Very content heavy course but her lectures are engaging and well thought out. Her exams (if you properly prepare and study aka memorize all the terms) reflect the course well and are easy to ace. I highly recommend this prof if you have the chance to take her.

Reading the comments I was scared to take her class but she is by far my favorite teacher I've ever had. hat being said, her lectures only cover the big parts of the chapter so you need to stay on top of things and actually read the chapter. Also make sure you use key words in definitions. It really is an easy class if you put the effort in
She is a really good prof, all you have to do is to take her notes, read the textbook and find a reliable case group and then you will ace this course.

Kind of arrogant, doesn't answer questions properly, makes the exams relatively easy but specifically marks them harder. Need to read the textbook because the slides won't help you, but you need to attend class in order to pass. She's slightly racist, you'll understand if you're colored. Do well on case studies to save your grade.
Just study the slides and you'll be fine, show up to class and do the activities and you get an easy 10% overall bird class if you study a bit

She's an incredibly tough grader. I do well in school and I struggled in her class, as her grading criteria demands very specific key words. Use other words to say the same thing and you won't pass. She's also very harsh on class participation. I was an average student, answered a couple questions and skipped a few 8:30ams and failed that section.

Amazing professor! Her lectures were great and she made uninteresting topics interesting. There's lots of group work so be prepared for that. Lecture notes aren't posted online but are similar to the textbook. No assignments but had easy case studies that required some thinking. Midterm and final were light work if you studied. Recommend for sure!
she is a wonderful teacher, a nice person and always prepared for class. You have to go to lectures to take notes because she does not put power points on brightspace.

Very caring and friendly prof. Cares about her students and puts a lot of effort into her lectures. Lectures aren't 100% necessary, but there are in-class cases and some exam questions are based on in-class activities. Be sure to be extremely specific on test questions. Use exact definitions and points otherwise you'll lose marks. Otherwise, easy A

Excellent prof. She really cares about her students and her lectures are engaging. You will have to show up for class because she doesn't post her slides, but the course follows the textbook anyways. Be very specific in your short answers on the midterm. The grading is tough since they look for key words.
Great prof! Classes were always interesting and her activities allowed everyone to stay engaged! Would take her if you can!

She's a boring lecturer and a bit arrogant when answering questions that challenged the material. She knows the material very well but just paraphrases her slides without offering insight or additional information. She's unflexible with the online portion of the class. I switched in late and missed two quizzes and she refused to let me try them.
Tough midterm and inconsiderate of homework deadlines, avoid!

Very easy to follow, lectures were extremely well structured and delivered; she is highly familiar with the course content and is obviously passionate about it. If you do your readings (very easy to skim through the textbook and grasp the main concepts) on top of the lectures, you can quite easily pass with an A. She also provides a lot of feedback
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Clear grading criteria', 'Accessible outside class']

rComments: Her midterms/finals are based 99% from the textbook and 1% from in-class activities (Obviously not accurate but it's just for reference). No slides posted, but you don't HAVE to go to every class if you're good at memorizing the whole textbook. Watch out for in-class activities, and definitely go to her pre-midterm/final review. Really nice prof!
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Participation matters', 'Gives good feedback']

rComments: Really kind prof. She teaches a course that could often be pretty bland but does it pretty well. You have to take notes by hand since PPTs are not posted but it's the same way for all OB courses. Good teacher.

I give her a 2/5 because she was a really nice professor indeed. However, all she teaches in lectures were exactly based from the textbook word for word. Study the textbook because her notes aren't helpful enough. You have to know your stuff or else you'll do bad.
just read the textbook and come to class. her question are something you would know. if you were frequent in class.

Good professor who is clear about exam expectations and does her best to prepare you. Even if you don't show up for class, you can still learn the material well as she bases the tests 100% from the textbook - but DO show up for class activities (sometimes tested in exams) and of course, group case studies. Easy course, but learn the terms well.

Best professor I ever had, she is very organized, very knowledgable and very friendly. Attendance was mandatory though because she doesn't post her slides online, but it wasn't that bad since she always manages to keep lectures fun and interesting.

She is an amazing prof. She puts effort in making classes interesting. She doesn't post her slides online. Work load is light, mostly test and exam, no assignments. Group work is necessary. Test is fair and heavily based on  class lectures. She has a terrible marker. Her marker looks for exact words and follows the making scheme blindly.
Amazing prof! Very clear and tries to make the topics interesting with many in-class activities. Study her notes very carefully for midterms, key words in definitions get you points.
Very clear teacher. Also, she is very easy to listen to. She made, what should have been a snooze fest, actually really enjoyable.

Professor Elliott is AMAZING! I am taking her again for HR. Beware that her slides are not posted on BBL so you HAVE to attend lectures and take notes. Lectures are great, exams are fair, and if you're nice to her she'll go the extra mile to help you! What she stresses in class is what's on the exams!

She's a great prof! I would recommend her to anyone who is taking OB. Probably the best prof I've had till now. She's a fair marker and the cases are easy. Her classes are fun and she's super sweet. Be sure to stay on top of your notes and you'll pass this class easily !!

Amazing prof. Very clear with what is on exams and makes a very boring class interesting. Definitely try to get her for OB if you can, she answers all questions you have clearly and her slides are almost all you need to study unless she mentions something in the textbook to read. MEMORIZE EXACT DEFINITIONS!
+Really nice +Straight forward lecture +Midterm and final reflects what is in the slides  -Lots of In class group project -Slides are not posted, thus you should come to class
The professor is amazing and should be "Go-to" for anyone who is taking ADM2336 and ADM2337. Her TAs are very picky though so be prepared to learn the textbook word-by-word.

She is a really nice prof. Midterms is based on ppt notes. Notes are not posted, so make sure attend classes. There are movies reference as well on the midterm.  Make sure to find good teammates as well.

Very nice person and engaging in class. Expects word for word definitions which is ridiculous, you will lose a lot of marks if you try and learn it yourself.  Also gives .25 marks out, not even .5 which is also strange. I wish I took the course with someone else personally. Memorization is key in this course.

Wow... I don't even know where to begin. Professor Elliott is absolutely amazing. She is fair, lectures are amazing and she is such a kind woman to talk to. She will help you succeed. The final is difficult as it's Department assigned but her mid-terms are very fair if you follow the lectures. You will WANT to attend her lectures!!

Prof Elliott is a great professor. Follows the book closely but still has engaging lectures. Midterms are fair. The final is multiple choice and cumulative so it's tough but the case studies are simple and in-class so they're easy and not time consuming. Two thumbs up!

She is a great professor but she expects you to word for word quote the definitions. All other profs accept deifinitons written in your own words. she doesn't care about grade revision requests. Shes an awesome prof but she and her TAs needs to show leniency in students own words. As long as the meaning gets across, it SHOULD be accepted.
The course material isn't very interesting, but her lectures are amazing. This course is all memorization. She's a grader, make sure you memorize your definitions and check your spelling.

Professor Elliott is THE BEST. She is genuinely helpful and always there to help with everything. She has this personality where you can go up to her and feel like you've known her all along. She is actually the single best example of how a prof should be. If only other profs could learn from her! She is highly inspirational with sold experience.

Professor Elliott is an amazing professor! She made business fun and engaging! Her case studies and activities put theories into practice. The midterms and exams were all fair and its very possible to do well if you study hard. The review sessions were also helpful, and she goes over the midterms! She's an absolutely wonderful person!

BEST PROF EVER!!!! She is always there to hep you, her assignments are easy mark, her exams are fair, her expectations are crystal clear, her review sessions are FUN and useful. Not only she is an amazing prof, but she is also a sweet, kind, nice human being!!! Take her for Human Resources and Organizational Behaviour. You will be happy you did.
Very fair and nice prof. The  midterms, cases and the final reflects everything in the textbook.
She's great! Her lectures are interesting and worth while. Read the textbook and do well on the midterms and cases before walking into the 80 MC final.
She was really nice and always helpful if you asked nicely. Her exams are not hard if you attend all her classes which are all not boring either.
She is so nice and wonderful! Super fair midterms and finals. Study the textbook well and case studies are straight forward. Love her classes and her happy teaching :D You'll love her for suree~!
AMAZING!!!! take any class you can with her so helpful and friendly! Favorite prof i have had in my 3 years here!

Dr. Elliot has to be one of the best professors I've ever taken. Very nice, professional, knowledgeable. Her classes are interesting, case studies and midterms are fair. I'd definitely take OB and Human Resource Mgnt with her if you can!

Great Prof, Extremely nice and easy to approach. Always smiling, loves her job, loves to interact the students. She does not provide notes online so go to class. Her exams are straight forward, no surprises, but really definition heavy and straight from the text.
